Name: nephroblastoma
Definition: A kidney cancer that affects the kidneys and typically located_in children.

Name: kidney hemangiopericytoma
Definition: A kidney cancer which is manifested in the kidney.

Name: obsolete ductal
Definition: A kidney cancer which is manifested in the kidney.

Name: childhood kidney cancer
Definition: A embryonal cancer that is located in the kidney.

Name: kidney sarcoma
Definition: A kidney cancer that is located in the kidney's connective tissue.

Name: obsolete extraskeletal cartilaginous and osseous tumor
Definition: A kidney cancer that is located in the kidney's connective tissue.

Name: obsolete malignant mediastinal mesenchymal tumor
Definition: A kidney cancer that is located in the kidney's connective tissue.
Synonym: malignant soft tissue tumor of mediastinum

Name: mesoblastic nephroma
Definition: A kidney cancer that is found in the kidney and is usually found before birth by ultrasound or within the first 3 months of life.

Name: malignant cystic nephroma
Definition: A vulva carcinoma that derives_from sweat glands and is characterized by the presence of clear cells.
